quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  21,112,"He (Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) said: "
  23,64,"Until when We seize those of them who lead a luxurious life with punishment: behold they make humble invocation with a loud voice."
  23,65,"Invoke not loudly this day! Certainly you shall not be helped by Us."
  23,66,"Indeed My Verses used to be recited to you, but you used to turn back on your heels (denying them, and refusing with hatred to listen to them)."
  24,46,"We have indeed sent down (in this Qur’ân) manifest Ayât (proofs, evidence, verses, lessons, signs, revelations, lawful and unlawful things, and the set boundaries of Islâmic religion, etc. that make things clear showing the Right Path of Allâh). And Allâh guides whom He wills to the Straight Path (i.e. to Allâh’s religion of Islâmic Monotheism)."
  24,47,"They (hypocrites) say: "
  24,48,"And when they are called to Allâh (i.e. His Words, the Qur’ân) and His Messenger (صلى الله عليه وسلم), to judge between them, lo! a party of them refuses (to come) and turns away."
  25,10,"Blessed be He Who, if He wills will assign you better than (all) that - Gardens under which rivers flow (Paradise) and will assign you palaces (i.e. in Paradise)."
  25,11,"Nay, they deny the Hour (the Day of Resurrection), and for those who deny the Hour, We have prepared a flaming Fire (i.e. Hell)."
  25,12,"When it (Hell) sees them from a far place, they will hear its raging and its roaring."